The High Court has ordered former Nairobi Governor Evans Kidero to pay the taxman Sh427,269,795. The ruling by Justice David Majanja followed an audit by the Commissioner for Domestic Taxes on the financial and business affairs of the former governor. Despite the former governor and the Commissioner reaching a consensus that funds raised for political party campaigns are not chargeable to tax, both parties failed to agree on whether Kidero, who was then vying for the Nairobi governor seat, had demonstrated the funds raised had actually been expended in political campaigns. More to follow